1
00:01:24,292 --> 00:01:26,461
Gosh… Hey.

2
00:01:26,544 --> 00:01:27,629
EPISODE 11

3
00:01:27,712 --> 00:01:31,466
How am I supposed to understand
a camera drone flying outside my window?

4
00:01:31,549 --> 00:01:32,675
I'm so sorry.

5
00:01:32,759 --> 00:01:35,178
We have looked into the drone

6
00:01:35,261 --> 00:01:38,848
and confirmed that a TV station flew
the drone while filming a drama.

7
00:01:38,932 --> 00:01:41,100
We requested them to halt the shoot. So--

8
00:01:41,184 --> 00:01:42,977
Is that the best you can do?

9
00:01:43,061 --> 00:01:45,104
You should check what's been filmed!

10
00:01:45,188 --> 00:01:48,733
Of course, sir.
We will review all of the footage.

11
00:01:48,817 --> 00:01:51,110
-If we come across anything that--
-No.

12
00:01:52,403 --> 00:01:54,322
I want to check it myself.

13
00:01:54,405 --> 00:01:55,740
You say you'll check it,

14
00:01:55,824 --> 00:01:58,243
but how can I be sure
you won't keep a video of me?

15
00:01:58,326 --> 00:02:00,870
Tell those TV station jerks
who flew that drone

16
00:02:00,954 --> 00:02:02,580
to call me directly

17
00:02:03,164 --> 00:02:04,499
and bring the original clips…

18
00:02:04,582 --> 00:02:06,334
Yesterday, they smeared the carpet

19
00:02:06,417 --> 00:02:09,337
with ketchup, gochujang, and fake blood.

20
00:02:09,420 --> 00:02:11,589
And they secretly flew a drone today.

21
00:02:11,673 --> 00:02:15,385
Despite all this trouble, I still can't
write that the production crew is

22
00:02:15,468 --> 00:02:17,387
-going crazy in my report?
-No, you can't.

23
00:02:17,971 --> 00:02:19,722
How do you deal with a day like today?

24
00:02:19,806 --> 00:02:22,851
We've been getting yelled at all day.
What do you do?

25
00:02:24,102 --> 00:02:27,939
I think about eating something spicy later
and getting my energy up.

26
00:02:28,523 --> 00:02:30,984
Or I think about things
that make me happy.

27
00:02:31,568 --> 00:02:33,194
This is why I should date.

28
00:02:33,278 --> 00:02:36,072
"I'm having such a hard day.
Can't you kiddie me?"

29
00:02:38,116 --> 00:02:40,743
You meant to say "baby" you.
Not "kiddie" you.

30
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:02,932
-Hey.
-Hey.

31
00:03:03,016 --> 00:03:05,435
Are you busy? Can we talk now?

32
00:03:05,518 --> 00:03:07,145
Okay. Bye.

33
00:03:07,812 --> 00:03:08,813
Hey. What was…

34
00:03:09,522 --> 00:03:11,149
Hey, you're just leaving?

35
00:03:11,232 --> 00:03:13,860
You said it was urgent. Young-do.

36
00:03:14,569 --> 00:03:17,739
Yes, Ms. Kang. I'm not busy at all.

37
00:03:18,573 --> 00:03:19,449
Young-do?

38
00:03:20,033 --> 00:03:21,075
Ju Young-do.

39
00:03:21,618 --> 00:03:23,411
No. No one is calling me.

40
00:03:24,370 --> 00:03:26,164
Right. You misheard it.

41
00:03:26,998 --> 00:03:30,293
Me? I was bored.

42
00:03:30,376 --> 00:03:32,378
I was hoping to get a phone call.

43
00:03:33,046 --> 00:03:35,214
No. Not at all.

44
00:03:35,298 --> 00:03:37,091
What could be wrong?

45
00:03:37,634 --> 00:03:38,593
I just thought of…

46
00:03:42,931 --> 00:03:45,183
Just because. No reason.

47
00:03:47,769 --> 00:03:50,313
No. I'll get off work late today.

48
00:03:50,813 --> 00:03:54,651
And Eun-ha and Ms. Ahn are
coming over to have dinner tonight.

49
00:03:56,694 --> 00:04:00,490
I see. I'll call you later then.

50
00:04:01,074 --> 00:04:03,326
I…

51
00:04:04,827 --> 00:04:06,079
miss…

52
00:04:06,913 --> 00:04:07,997
I…

53
00:04:09,290 --> 00:04:10,833
Okay. Bye.

54
00:04:20,843 --> 00:04:22,011
Gosh.

55
00:04:26,891 --> 00:04:28,184
Did you hear everything?

56
00:04:29,769 --> 00:04:32,146
I'm not sure if I heard anything.

57
00:04:32,939 --> 00:04:34,857
I'm relieved if you didn't hear anything.

58
00:04:34,941 --> 00:04:37,068
"So you won't be able to see me today.

59
00:04:37,151 --> 00:04:40,863
Darn. Why do they
always come over to your house?

60
00:04:41,823 --> 00:04:44,450
I wish you and I were living together.

61
00:04:44,534 --> 00:04:47,829
I hope I can see you tomorrow."

62
00:04:47,912 --> 00:04:50,206
But you couldn't say this,
so you ended up saying,

63
00:04:50,290 --> 00:04:52,375
"I… miss…"

64
00:04:56,379 --> 00:04:58,589
Please don't tell anyone.

65
00:04:59,173 --> 00:05:00,883
It's not an affair or a crime.

66
00:05:01,592 --> 00:05:03,136
Right. That's true, but…

67
00:05:03,219 --> 00:05:06,472
If anything goes south,
are you going to back out right away?

68
00:05:06,556 --> 00:05:07,765
No. That's not it.

69
00:05:07,849 --> 00:05:08,683
"Oh, dear."

70
00:05:16,441 --> 00:05:20,903
I want to be considerate of Ms. Kang.
I want to be careful.

71
00:05:26,117 --> 00:05:27,577
This way.

72
00:05:29,620 --> 00:05:31,914
Right. You're busy, right?
Please get back to work.

73
00:05:50,349 --> 00:05:52,518
FORENSIC INVESTIGATION

74
00:05:59,901 --> 00:06:01,819
Yes. I'm at the scene.

75
00:06:11,204 --> 00:06:13,164
Your lawyer isn't here yet.

76
00:06:13,247 --> 00:06:14,874
Are you sure you want to start now?

77
00:06:15,625 --> 00:06:16,626
Yes.

78
00:06:18,336 --> 00:06:21,506
As soon as you came to the station,
you requested a drug test.

79
00:06:21,589 --> 00:06:22,799
Why did you do that?

80
00:06:22,882 --> 00:06:25,760
I needed to get tested
before the drug went out of my system.

81
00:06:25,843 --> 00:06:28,262
How were you so sure you'd been drugged?

82
00:06:28,346 --> 00:06:31,349
After I came home,
the liquor was the only thing I drank.

83
00:06:31,933 --> 00:06:34,060
But it had no distinct smell or color,

84
00:06:34,143 --> 00:06:36,270
and it took me three hours to wake up.

85
00:06:37,522 --> 00:06:40,066
So I deduced that it must be GHB.

86
00:06:43,194 --> 00:06:47,698
Someone entered your house
and spiked your liquor with some drug?

87
00:06:48,699 --> 00:06:50,910
What makes you think so?

88
00:06:52,036 --> 00:06:54,247
Once you eliminate the wrong answer,

89
00:06:54,330 --> 00:06:56,499
that's the only possible answer left.

90
00:06:57,500 --> 00:07:00,294
That Ian Chase killed Noh Hyeon-ju.

91
00:07:01,879 --> 00:07:03,422
So that's the wrong answer, right?

92
00:07:04,590 --> 00:07:05,508
Yes.

93
00:07:06,592 --> 00:07:08,386
That's not what happened.

94
00:07:11,764 --> 00:07:13,933
Today at 1:40 a.m.,

95
00:07:14,016 --> 00:07:17,645
you and Ms. Noh Hyeon-ju went

96
00:07:18,771 --> 00:07:19,856
into your place.

97
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:21,399
Is that correct?

98
00:07:21,482 --> 00:07:22,316
Yes.

99
00:07:23,192 --> 00:07:24,777
Just do what you've been doing.

100
00:07:25,528 --> 00:07:26,737
That's all you need to do.

101
00:08:05,693 --> 00:08:09,071
They do it because they think
by crossing the line just this once,

102
00:08:09,572 --> 00:08:11,824
they'll be able to live

103
00:08:11,908 --> 00:08:15,161
normal and stable lives
like everyone else.

104
00:08:29,008 --> 00:08:30,134
A shadow…

105
00:08:31,719 --> 00:08:33,679
shouldn't covet the light.

106
00:08:35,473 --> 00:08:36,682
Because it'll vanish.

107
00:08:44,524 --> 00:08:46,234
VIOLENT CRIMES TEAM 3
KO JIN-BOK

108
00:09:05,211 --> 00:09:06,587
Detective Ko Jin-bok.

109
00:09:09,632 --> 00:09:11,342
A woman has died.

110
00:09:13,761 --> 00:09:15,805
How did you get that wound on your hand?

111
00:09:18,891 --> 00:09:20,977
This has nothing to do with this incident.

112
00:09:21,060 --> 00:09:22,728
Could someone confirm that?

113
00:09:22,812 --> 00:09:23,938
Yes.

114
00:09:25,106 --> 00:09:25,940
Give me a name.

115
00:09:31,696 --> 00:09:35,241
Everyone in the hotel lobby that day
saw how I got this wound.

116
00:09:35,741 --> 00:09:39,453
Detective Park. Go to this hotel
and see if his story checks out.

117
00:09:39,537 --> 00:09:42,540
Get the footage
that captured how he hurt his hand too.

118
00:09:43,958 --> 00:09:47,503
The woman who brought Choi Jeong-min's
suicide note works at this hotel.

119
00:09:49,297 --> 00:09:50,506
Right.

120
00:09:51,632 --> 00:09:53,009
Ms. Kang works there.

121
00:09:53,092 --> 00:09:55,928
I have her number.
I'll ask her for the footage in advance.

122
00:09:56,012 --> 00:09:58,347
No, don't call her.
Go ask someone else there.

123
00:09:59,140 --> 00:10:00,057
Why?

124
00:10:00,141 --> 00:10:03,144
Our job is catching criminals.

125
00:10:03,227 --> 00:10:04,604
But we also meet people

126
00:10:04,687 --> 00:10:07,648
who go through horrible things
because of those criminals.

127
00:10:07,732 --> 00:10:09,734
And she already went through it once.

128
00:10:09,817 --> 00:10:12,361
Pretty recently because of
a guy who looks just like him.

129
00:10:13,779 --> 00:10:14,822
Right.

130
00:10:14,905 --> 00:10:17,658
Unless we need her statement
to confirm more things,

131
00:10:17,742 --> 00:10:20,286
let's ask someone else
to check out his statement.

132
00:10:20,369 --> 00:10:21,287
Okay.

133
00:10:22,330 --> 00:10:25,041
So you witnessed
the incident yourself. Correct?

134
00:10:25,124 --> 00:10:27,501
Yes. But what is this about?

135
00:10:27,585 --> 00:10:31,881
Do you have any record that I can use
to confirm the story?

136
00:10:31,964 --> 00:10:35,635
We have the daily log and the security
camera footage from the lobby.

137
00:10:35,718 --> 00:10:38,429
But I must know why you need them first.

138
00:10:38,512 --> 00:10:42,642
Well, we're investigating a homicide,
and that's all I can tell you.

139
00:10:42,725 --> 00:10:43,809
A homicide?

140
00:10:44,393 --> 00:10:47,021
Are you telling me someone is dead?

141
00:10:48,272 --> 00:10:49,106
Yes.

142
00:11:20,137 --> 00:11:22,431
Detective Ko, we found a camera
at the crime scene.

143
00:11:22,932 --> 00:11:25,017
It transmits video feeds
without a memory card.

144
00:11:25,601 --> 00:11:27,520
Are you talking about a spy cam?

145
00:11:27,603 --> 00:11:29,105
Where was it facing?

146
00:11:31,857 --> 00:11:33,109
Do you have to ask?

147
00:11:33,192 --> 00:11:36,278
Ask the server company to cooperate.
If not, we'll get a warrant.

148
00:11:36,362 --> 00:11:37,571
Are you done at the scene?

149
00:11:38,364 --> 00:11:41,158
Yes. Wrap up and come back.
I'll wrap up and head back too.

150
00:11:41,951 --> 00:11:43,035
You're saying

151
00:11:43,536 --> 00:11:46,622
Ms. Noh never drank this liquor. Correct?

152
00:11:47,206 --> 00:11:48,082
Yes.

153
00:11:50,042 --> 00:11:53,963
Then if the drink was spiked,
the culprit was after you.

154
00:11:54,046 --> 00:11:57,842
But you were unconscious
for 3 hours from 2:28 a.m.

155
00:11:57,925 --> 00:12:00,886
That gives plenty of time
for the culprit to kill you.

156
00:12:01,846 --> 00:12:04,348
But the culprit killed
Ms. Noh who wasn't the target

157
00:12:04,432 --> 00:12:05,808
and left the scene?

158
00:12:09,270 --> 00:12:12,148
How often did Ms. Noh visit your studio?

159
00:12:12,898 --> 00:12:14,483
Almost every day.

160
00:12:14,567 --> 00:12:16,110
Even the day before the incident?

161
00:12:16,193 --> 00:12:17,820
-Yes.
-Why?

162
00:12:18,446 --> 00:12:21,031
I asked her to get something for me,
so she brought it.

163
00:12:21,115 --> 00:12:22,992
What did you ask her to get for you?

164
00:12:23,075 --> 00:12:24,076
A dissertation.

165
00:12:24,160 --> 00:12:25,536
A dissertation?

166
00:12:27,288 --> 00:12:29,415
What is the title?

167
00:12:30,875 --> 00:12:34,712
Trauma That Leads to Sadism.
That's the title.

168
00:12:37,506 --> 00:12:42,052
I also brought copies
of two of Ju Young-do's dissertations.

169
00:12:50,186 --> 00:12:52,146
TRAUMA THAT LEADS TO SADISM
BY JU YOUNG-DO

170
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:57,651
People who resort to violence
because they were consumed by rage

171
00:12:57,735 --> 00:12:59,612
or intoxicated with alcohol

172
00:12:59,695 --> 00:13:02,907
realize once their rage
or the alcohol wears off

173
00:13:06,494 --> 00:13:10,831
that the person they wanted to hurt
was themselves.

174
00:13:11,540 --> 00:13:14,001
It could be them
in the present circumstances.

175
00:13:14,084 --> 00:13:17,296
Or it could be their old selves
who made mistakes.

176
00:13:18,088 --> 00:13:22,051
Uncontrollable aggression
is an expression of self-contempt.

177
00:13:23,552 --> 00:13:26,639
Why do we pay attention
to how criminals feel?

178
00:13:27,223 --> 00:13:29,558
Why do we leave room for understanding?

179
00:13:30,184 --> 00:13:34,730
To answer those questions,
I must start with the following.

180
00:13:35,231 --> 00:13:39,610
Because they are bound
to be someone's neighbor,

181
00:13:40,110 --> 00:13:42,905
we cannot give up on correcting
and reforming their behaviors,

182
00:13:42,988 --> 00:13:44,782
and forgiving them in order to coexist.

183
00:13:45,282 --> 00:13:49,078
We must find the moment that the darkest
and weakest beings of society,

184
00:13:49,787 --> 00:13:53,165
who never received the slightest help,

185
00:13:53,249 --> 00:13:56,585
turn into criminals.

186
00:13:58,128 --> 00:14:01,465
They do it because they think
by crossing the line just this once,

187
00:14:02,049 --> 00:14:03,801
they'll be able to live

188
00:14:04,552 --> 00:14:07,555
normal and stable lives
like everyone else.

189
00:14:09,974 --> 00:14:11,934
Therefore, we must help them

190
00:14:13,561 --> 00:14:17,064
stay away from the water plant
that keeps dragging them down

191
00:14:17,147 --> 00:14:20,067
no matter how hard they try to escape.

192
00:14:25,155 --> 00:14:29,159
Is there any reason that you moved
into Choi Jeong-min's old studio?

193
00:14:36,041 --> 00:14:37,209
Mr. Chase.

194
00:14:44,550 --> 00:14:46,510
Why did you move into that studio?

195
00:14:50,097 --> 00:14:51,515
I would like…

196
00:14:54,143 --> 00:14:55,686
to talk to Mr. Ju Young-do.

197
00:15:06,363 --> 00:15:07,990
Can I ask you something?

198
00:15:08,073 --> 00:15:08,908
Sure.

199
00:15:10,159 --> 00:15:13,203
You're not exclusive
with Dr. Chase, right?

200
00:15:13,287 --> 00:15:16,916
You're just casually seeing him, right?
It's nothing serious. Right?

201
00:15:18,208 --> 00:15:21,712
I'm not dating him.
What made you think so?

202
00:15:21,795 --> 00:15:25,299
I saw you getting into his car,
and you bought men's clothes that day.

203
00:15:25,382 --> 00:15:28,052
When you got text messages,
your eyes gleamed with love.

204
00:15:28,719 --> 00:15:31,722
It wasn't a date.
And the shirt wasn't for him.

205
00:15:32,556 --> 00:15:34,308
-Really?
-Yes.

206
00:15:39,313 --> 00:15:40,522
By the way,

207
00:15:42,191 --> 00:15:43,651
do you feel okay

208
00:15:44,568 --> 00:15:46,028
around him?

209
00:15:46,612 --> 00:15:50,616
If you're really not dating him,
can I give you my honest answer?

210
00:15:50,699 --> 00:15:51,617
Sure.

211
00:15:52,868 --> 00:15:54,286
He scares me.

212
00:15:54,870 --> 00:15:56,580
He grabbed the knife with his hand.

213
00:15:56,664 --> 00:15:59,750
And he's got this dark aura around him.

214
00:15:59,833 --> 00:16:03,128
So I wondered why you were dating him.

215
00:16:03,212 --> 00:16:06,465
I just thought that there was
a side of him I hadn't seen yet.

216
00:16:08,717 --> 00:16:11,261
I haven't seen that side either.

217
00:16:12,888 --> 00:16:14,556
I didn't want to feel this way.

218
00:16:16,183 --> 00:16:18,060
But I'm scared of him too now.

219
00:16:18,143 --> 00:16:20,562
So you're really not dating him, right?

220
00:16:21,063 --> 00:16:22,189
No.

221
00:16:22,272 --> 00:16:23,983
Then what was that look I saw before?

222
00:16:26,402 --> 00:16:30,656
Well, there's someone I like.
It was for him.

223
00:16:31,407 --> 00:16:33,033
Are you sure it's not Dr. Chase?

224
00:16:33,951 --> 00:16:35,077
Yes, I am.

225
00:16:36,495 --> 00:16:37,830
What's this about?

226
00:16:39,748 --> 00:16:40,582
Nothing.

227
00:16:43,544 --> 00:16:46,005
If there is anything, you have to tell me.

228
00:16:46,088 --> 00:16:48,424
You're on my team,
so you're my responsibility.

229
00:16:49,008 --> 00:16:53,804
Helping you with problems you face at work
is also part of my job.

230
00:16:54,763 --> 00:16:56,432
Seriously. You're Kang Sweet.

231
00:16:56,515 --> 00:16:58,392
Gosh. No. Not this.

232
00:17:00,644 --> 00:17:02,896
By the way, who's the guy you like?

233
00:17:04,106 --> 00:17:05,899
-He's a good person.
-Is he handsome?

234
00:17:05,983 --> 00:17:07,359
-Yes.
-Do you have his photo?

235
00:17:07,443 --> 00:17:08,736
-No.
-What about a video?

236
00:17:14,283 --> 00:17:17,161
See? You were the only one
who didn't put a finger down.

237
00:17:17,244 --> 00:17:19,580
So what?
You were lying when you put yours down.

238
00:17:20,581 --> 00:17:21,832
I did kiss someone.

239
00:17:22,416 --> 00:17:23,792
My finger told the truth.

240
00:17:23,876 --> 00:17:25,836
Just believe me.
I'll bet his life savings.

241
00:17:25,919 --> 00:17:28,714
Who said you could do that?
Did you really kiss someone?

242
00:17:29,298 --> 00:17:31,050
When, where, why, with whom, and how?

243
00:17:32,259 --> 00:17:33,802
A gentleman doesn't kiss and tell.

244
00:17:33,886 --> 00:17:35,262
Gosh.

245
00:17:35,345 --> 00:17:39,016
I'm not interested in your personal life,
but I must get to the bottom of this.

246
00:17:39,725 --> 00:17:41,310
So this thing you did,

247
00:17:41,894 --> 00:17:44,271
it wasn't illegal or unethical, right?

248
00:17:45,272 --> 00:17:47,357
Of course not.

249
00:17:49,276 --> 00:17:50,402
What in the world?

250
00:17:50,486 --> 00:17:54,073
There really is a man who has never
been kissed in 38 years of his life?

251
00:17:54,156 --> 00:17:55,657
Is this true?

252
00:18:00,120 --> 00:18:00,954
Just eat.

253
00:18:01,622 --> 00:18:02,706
Yes, Detective Ko.

254
00:18:04,917 --> 00:18:06,210
Tomorrow night?

255
00:18:06,960 --> 00:18:08,462
Yes. I'll go to the station.

256
00:18:09,129 --> 00:18:10,756
But what's this about?

257
00:18:11,381 --> 00:18:12,716
No.

258
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:14,760
