come over to your house often?

517
00:35:54,735 --> 00:35:57,530
Oh. You don't have to worry about that.

518
00:35:57,613 --> 00:35:59,949
Seung-won will be editing all night.
I checked.

519
00:36:00,992 --> 00:36:01,826
You checked?

520
00:36:03,953 --> 00:36:07,582
No. I didn't do that on purpose.

521
00:36:07,665 --> 00:36:09,792
Seung-won calls and texts me often.

522
00:36:09,876 --> 00:36:13,963
I mean, he even sends me
photos of his meals. What's with him?

523
00:36:14,505 --> 00:36:19,302
I even wondered if this is
a case of relationship addiction.

524
00:36:19,385 --> 00:36:21,470
But with relationship addiction,

525
00:36:21,554 --> 00:36:24,849
one's self-esteem becomes low
when the other person keeps ignoring them.

526
00:36:24,932 --> 00:36:27,852
But this jerk…
But his self-esteem doesn't.

527
00:36:28,603 --> 00:36:33,691
In that case, I can only conclude that
he's trying to gain social interest.

528
00:36:33,774 --> 00:36:37,987
He needs to get
a lot of attention even if it's shallow.

529
00:36:38,070 --> 00:36:41,032
With that conclusion,
he found a job that suits his needs.

530
00:36:41,115 --> 00:36:45,203
So what exactly did you say
to check if he'd come over or not?

531
00:36:47,914 --> 00:36:49,415
You're not coming over, right?

532
00:36:49,498 --> 00:36:50,875
Not today, right?

533
00:36:50,958 --> 00:36:52,835
You're not, right?

534
00:36:53,753 --> 00:36:54,754
Gosh.

535
00:36:55,630 --> 00:36:57,006
You got a text message.

536
00:37:00,218 --> 00:37:01,427
You got a text message.

537
00:37:02,261 --> 00:37:04,055
If he misses me, he should just say it.

538
00:37:04,889 --> 00:37:06,724
-You got a text message.
-Who is it?

539
00:37:06,807 --> 00:37:07,850
Someone I know.

540
00:37:10,144 --> 00:37:12,396
-Do you miss me?
-If you come over, I'll kill you.

541
00:37:12,480 --> 00:37:13,522
-I'll come over.
-Don't.

542
00:37:13,606 --> 00:37:14,523
Seriously?

543
00:37:15,107 --> 00:37:16,317
No, I have an all-nighter.

544
00:37:16,400 --> 00:37:19,237
I edited out boring parts,
so I'm left with a six-minute video.

545
00:37:19,946 --> 00:37:23,032
Oh, right. I sent you a package. Open it.

546
00:37:23,115 --> 00:37:24,283
Half of it is yours.

547
00:37:38,297 --> 00:37:39,340
Come on in.

548
00:37:44,512 --> 00:37:47,390
So this is what your place looks like.

549
00:37:48,516 --> 00:37:50,434
Nothing has changed since last time.

550
00:37:51,102 --> 00:37:53,896
I didn't have time
to look around your house that night.

551
00:37:53,980 --> 00:37:55,106
Why…

552
00:37:56,023 --> 00:37:58,776
Right. I'm sorry.

553
00:37:58,859 --> 00:38:00,319
-Please sit.
-Okay.

554
00:38:02,613 --> 00:38:04,240
What would you like to drink?

555
00:38:04,323 --> 00:38:06,242
-Water, please.
-Water.

556
00:38:12,498 --> 00:38:14,208
What's in the package?

557
00:38:15,876 --> 00:38:17,837
Actually, I was going to open it to see.

558
00:38:21,173 --> 00:38:22,550
Here you go.

559
00:38:22,633 --> 00:38:24,176
Thank you.

560
00:38:30,266 --> 00:38:32,685
THE VIRILITY KING

561
00:38:34,729 --> 00:38:35,771
What's this?

562
00:38:36,397 --> 00:38:37,606
THE VIRILITY KING

563
00:38:49,243 --> 00:38:51,620
"In Dongui Bogam, silky bush clover

564
00:38:51,704 --> 00:38:54,290
is recorded as the Virility King.

565
00:38:54,790 --> 00:38:58,044
This herb is known
to increase virility during the night.

566
00:38:58,127 --> 00:39:01,964
Those of you who dream of
becoming the ruler of the steamy night…"

567
00:39:03,257 --> 00:39:05,551
That's what this is?

568
00:39:06,677 --> 00:39:08,846
You must know better since you ordered it.

569
00:39:10,890 --> 00:39:11,891
Wait.

570
00:39:13,851 --> 00:39:15,186
It's not mine.

571
00:39:15,269 --> 00:39:17,313
I don't even drink alcohol. Why would I…

572
00:39:21,400 --> 00:39:23,652
"It's very effective
if you make tea with it."

573
00:39:26,072 --> 00:39:28,074
Right. I can just show you the texts.

574
00:39:31,786 --> 00:39:33,287
Look. Read this.

575
00:39:33,371 --> 00:39:34,538
See? I didn't order it.

576
00:39:34,622 --> 00:39:36,582
Oh, right. I sent you a package. Open it.

577
00:39:36,665 --> 00:39:37,708
Half of it is yours.

578
00:39:37,792 --> 00:39:39,752
IF YOU COME OVER, I'LL KILL YOU

579
00:39:40,252 --> 00:39:41,670
You're not coming over, right?

580
00:39:41,754 --> 00:39:44,757
Not today, right? You're not, right?

581
00:39:45,424 --> 00:39:48,052
You did check multiple times.

582
00:39:48,803 --> 00:39:49,887
Oh, dear.

583
00:39:55,059 --> 00:39:56,310
Our food is here.

584
00:39:56,977 --> 00:39:58,729
I'm glad we ordered it on our way.

585
00:40:00,106 --> 00:40:01,690
Okay. Please come on up.

586
00:40:05,903 --> 00:40:07,113
All right.

587
00:40:16,831 --> 00:40:19,041
NOTICE OF SUCCESSION

588
00:40:19,125 --> 00:40:20,751
I came because of that,

589
00:40:21,669 --> 00:40:23,087
but she's not home.

590
00:40:24,505 --> 00:40:25,756
You should have called.

591
00:40:25,840 --> 00:40:27,967
If I did, she would've asked why I called.

592
00:40:28,634 --> 00:40:30,678
Then I would've told her everything.

593
00:40:31,595 --> 00:40:33,722
But I thought I should tell her in person.

594
00:40:35,599 --> 00:40:37,017
You're right.

595
00:40:37,101 --> 00:40:37,977
Should I just

596
00:40:39,186 --> 00:40:40,479
not tell her?

597
00:40:41,063 --> 00:40:44,233
What are you talking about?
She ought to know too.

598
00:40:44,817 --> 00:40:47,027
You should tell her,
even if it's over the phone.

599
00:40:59,874 --> 00:41:03,669
You must be bored.
There's nothing to do here.

600
00:41:03,752 --> 00:41:04,753
Want to watch TV?

601
00:41:05,337 --> 00:41:06,338
No.

602
00:41:06,422 --> 00:41:09,341
Okay. It won't take long.

603
00:41:13,762 --> 00:41:14,597
It's ready.

604
00:41:15,389 --> 00:41:16,432
All right.

605
00:41:17,308 --> 00:41:19,393
-Here you go.
-Thank you.

606
00:41:24,356 --> 00:41:25,900
This is good.

607
00:41:27,276 --> 00:41:29,653
I don't know
what other people do to host guests.

608
00:41:29,737 --> 00:41:31,238
There's not much to do here.

609
00:41:33,073 --> 00:41:34,450
Is the chair comfortable?

610
00:41:34,533 --> 00:41:36,619
If you want to relax, you can lie down…

611
00:41:41,040 --> 00:41:42,124
Did I really say that?

612
00:41:43,417 --> 00:41:46,504
I didn't mean to say that. I…

613
00:41:46,587 --> 00:41:48,839
I don't have a sofa in the living room.

614
00:41:48,923 --> 00:41:50,841
I should go and buy one tomorrow.

615
00:41:50,925 --> 00:41:53,219
I was afraid the guys might
come over more often

616
00:41:53,302 --> 00:41:55,054
and sleep on it, so I didn't buy one.

617
00:41:55,137 --> 00:41:57,389
But I would've bought it
if I knew you'd be here.

618
00:41:57,473 --> 00:41:59,433
For you to lie down and relax…

619
00:42:01,018 --> 00:42:03,437
I did that again.
I'm not telling you to lie down.

620
00:42:04,772 --> 00:42:05,773
What's wrong with me?

621
00:42:08,817 --> 00:42:10,152
This chair is comfortable.

622
00:42:10,778 --> 00:42:11,946
Okay.

623
00:42:13,155 --> 00:42:16,033
You seem to be
the one feeling uncomfortable here.

624
00:42:17,243 --> 00:42:19,328
Do you know
you seem really flustered today?

625
00:42:20,746 --> 00:42:23,958
Right. I'm not usually like this.

626
00:42:24,041 --> 00:42:25,668
I rarely get taken aback too.

627
00:42:25,751 --> 00:42:29,713
But for some reason,
I have a lot on my mind today.

628
00:42:31,006 --> 00:42:33,008
I mean, not any weird thoughts.

629
00:42:37,805 --> 00:42:39,390
I should sit down here.

630
00:43:30,274 --> 00:43:31,317
Young-do.

631
00:43:35,654 --> 00:43:37,531
Nice. Coffee.

632
00:43:39,908 --> 00:43:41,201
Smells great.

633
00:43:44,246 --> 00:43:45,539
Are you in the bathroom?

634
00:43:47,958 --> 00:43:49,001
Young-do.

635
00:43:50,461 --> 00:43:53,005
-Young-do, where are you?
-But why are we hiding?

636
00:43:53,088 --> 00:43:54,590
I see ice cubes in the coffee.

637
00:43:56,634 --> 00:43:57,968
-Well…
-Young-do.

638
00:44:00,346 --> 00:44:02,973
Young-do, where are you?

639
00:44:03,891 --> 00:44:05,351
All the lights are on.

640
00:44:06,060 --> 00:44:07,436
Is he sick?

641
00:44:08,270 --> 00:44:10,773
YOUNG-DO

642
00:44:17,154 --> 00:44:19,198
THOUSAND WON

643
00:44:25,287 --> 00:44:27,790
-We should just go out now.
-No.

644
00:44:28,290 --> 00:44:30,334
He might get the wrong idea
if we go out now.

645
00:44:31,460 --> 00:44:33,337
Ha-neul, are you with Young-do now?

646
00:44:33,420 --> 00:44:36,215
He had a slight fever yesterday.
I wonder if he's sick again.

647
00:44:36,298 --> 00:44:37,758
I'm at his house now.

648
00:44:38,467 --> 00:44:40,260
I think he left in a hurry.

649
00:44:40,761 --> 00:44:44,264
The lights are on. And the ice cubes
in the coffee haven't melted yet.

650
00:44:49,770 --> 00:44:51,105
I see.

651
00:44:52,231 --> 00:44:53,399
Oh, dear.

652
00:44:53,982 --> 00:44:55,651
Young-do.

653
00:44:56,777 --> 00:44:58,654
Where are you?

654
00:44:59,655 --> 00:45:02,157
Are we playing hide-and-seek?

655
00:45:02,658 --> 00:45:06,453
Young-do, you're not in that room,
are you?

656
00:45:06,537 --> 00:45:08,539
I'm coming in.

657
00:45:12,334 --> 00:45:13,419
Why lock the door?

658
00:45:13,502 --> 00:45:15,003
He might come in.

659
00:45:15,087 --> 00:45:16,755
That makes it more suspicious.

660
00:45:21,468 --> 00:45:22,302
Young-do.

661
00:45:24,054 --> 00:45:26,432
I'm bored right now. Young-do.

662
00:45:27,724 --> 00:45:30,394
Gosh. I guess he's really not home.

663
00:45:32,229 --> 00:45:34,189
I should go and buy some beer.

664
00:45:34,273 --> 00:45:36,859
How come there's no beer here?

665
00:45:36,942 --> 00:45:38,694
How can there be a house without beer?

666
00:46:09,600 --> 00:46:10,809
Ta-da!

667
00:46:14,354 --> 00:46:15,397
Goodness.

668
00:46:18,484 --> 00:46:21,195
Young-do. Why did you close the door?

669
00:46:21,778 --> 00:46:23,071
Young-do, I'm scared.

670
00:46:23,155 --> 00:46:24,865
Why are there women's shoes here?

671
00:46:25,991 --> 00:46:27,117
Young-do.

672
00:46:32,623 --> 00:46:33,999
I'm sorry.

673
00:46:38,003 --> 00:46:39,004
Sorry.

674
00:46:48,722 --> 00:46:50,474
Why is he calling me?

675
00:46:51,642 --> 00:46:53,560
He's calling instead of texting?

676
00:46:58,148 --> 00:46:59,441
It's my brother.

677
00:47:00,192 --> 00:47:03,070
I see. Tae-jeong? You should answer it.

678
00:47:03,153 --> 00:47:04,154
Okay.

679
00:47:07,616 --> 00:47:08,617
Hey.

680
00:47:09,785 --> 00:47:11,620
Your address is set as Gangneung, right?

681
00:47:12,746 --> 00:47:14,206
Yes. Why do you ask?

682
00:47:14,289 --> 00:47:17,793
You know, our so-called father…

683
00:47:23,507 --> 00:47:24,508
Yes.

684
00:47:26,552 --> 00:47:27,928
I think he passed away.

685
00:47:31,223 --> 00:47:32,474
How do you know that?

686
00:47:34,518 --> 00:47:36,770
I received a notice of succession.

687
00:47:37,563 --> 00:47:41,608
It says we have to pay off the debts
left by him, the deceased.

688
00:47:42,359 --> 00:47:45,946
If yours went to Gangneung,
Mom must have already found out.

689
00:47:49,199 --> 00:47:50,284
Are you there?

690
00:47:53,412 --> 00:47:54,955
I'm listening.

691
00:47:57,541 --> 00:48:00,335
I'm getting off work early tomorrow.

692
00:48:00,419 --> 00:48:01,837
I'll go to Gangneung.

693
00:48:01,920 --> 00:48:04,214
I'll come with you. I should be there too.

694
00:48:05,257 --> 00:48:07,092
When are you leaving?

695
00:48:15,309 --> 00:48:17,853
KANG YE-SEONG LAW FIRM

696
00:48:17,936 --> 00:48:20,772
I want to take care of this
without my kids knowing.

697
00:48:22,149 --> 00:48:25,402
If it was sent to your daughter,
your son must have gotten it as well.

698
00:48:27,446 --> 00:48:28,655
Don't worry.

699
00:48:29,406 --> 00:48:33,452
When they renounce the succession,
they can file an objection to this notice.

700
00:48:40,208 --> 00:48:41,543
Here.

701
00:48:41,627 --> 00:48:43,754
This is Da-jeong's. That's yours.

702
00:48:44,504 --> 00:48:45,339
Thanks.

703
00:48:46,298 --> 00:48:49,343
Drive safely.
And take care of your mom too.

704
00:48:51,094 --> 00:48:53,597
And you should take care of yourself too.

705
00:48:54,348 --> 00:48:55,599
I'm fine.

706
00:48:56,266 --> 00:48:58,226
I'm going there for my sister and mom.

707
00:48:58,810 --> 00:48:59,811
Even so.

708
00:49:02,939 --> 00:49:05,525
I'm thinking about heading over
after I'm done with work.

709
00:49:05,609 --> 00:49:07,778
No. That's not necessary.

710
00:49:09,529 --> 00:49:13,116
I know you have patients tomorrow.
It will be tiring to go back and forth.

711
00:49:13,825 --> 00:49:16,036
That's not a problem.

712
00:49:19,164 --> 00:49:20,332
I'm just

713
00:49:21,249 --> 00:49:23,168
going there to see my mom.

714
00:49:29,633 --> 00:49:34,179
There's this line
from a movie called Incendies.

715
00:49:36,515 --> 00:49:39,309
"Childhood is like
a knife stuck in the throat

716
00:49:39,976 --> 00:49:42,104
which cannot be easily removed."

717
00:49:45,357 --> 00:49:46,483
I guess this year

718
00:49:47,317 --> 00:49:49,277
is the year I pull out that knife.

719
00:49:55,325 --> 00:49:59,162
But I already pulled
most of it out with you,

720
00:50:00,288 --> 00:50:02,999
so all there's left to do
is simply remove it.

721
00:50:06,712 --> 00:50:08,880
I'll pull it out easily
like a circus performer.

722
00:50:09,965 --> 00:50:11,174
Just like this.

723
00:50:14,970 --> 00:50:17,097
If you get too excited, you'll get hurt.

724
00:50:25,147 --> 00:50:28,734
Then the center took care of his funeral?

725
00:50:30,402 --> 00:50:31,445
I guess so.

726
00:50:33,655 --> 00:50:36,199
If it weren't for
the notice of succession,

727
00:50:36,283 --> 00:50:38,034
they wouldn't have known that he died.

728
00:50:39,870 --> 00:50:41,079
I guess.

729
00:50:42,956 --> 00:50:44,207
Shouldn't we go with them?

730
00:50:44,291 --> 00:50:46,501
Da-jeong was smiling when she left.

731
00:50:47,252 --> 00:50:50,005
She was begging us
not to make a fuss out of this.

732
00:50:52,424 --> 00:50:55,135
I feel bad that
no one was there when he died.

733
00:50:56,052 --> 00:50:57,471
Even I feel bad.

734
00:50:57,554 --> 00:50:59,473
She's going to need a lot of good fortune

735
00:50:59,556 --> 00:51:02,684
to break even with
all these misfortunes in her life.

736
00:51:11,568 --> 00:51:14,237
Thanks for driving.

737
00:51:14,321 --> 00:51:15,238
Sure.

738
00:51:16,698 --> 00:51:17,949
Let's go in.

739
00:51:18,909 --> 00:51:19,910
Okay.

740
00:51:27,542 --> 00:51:30,420
Go back to Seoul right away
after saying hi to Mom.

741
00:51:31,963 --> 00:51:33,215
You have work.

742
00:51:34,758 --> 00:51:38,386
It must've been hard to explain
why you needed a day off today.

743
00:51:40,764 --> 00:51:41,765
Okay.

744
00:51:45,435 --> 00:51:46,645
To tell the truth…

745
00:51:51,441 --> 00:51:52,818
I saw him once.

746
00:52:00,575 --> 00:52:01,576
When?

747
00:52:04,079 --> 00:52:05,497
When I was in seventh grade,

748
00:52:06,998 --> 00:52:09,417
I waited in front of your school.
Remember that?

749
00:52:10,794 --> 00:52:12,379
When I sprained my ankle.

750
00:52:16,341 --> 00:52:19,344
That winter when you came
to my school limping?

751
00:52:19,928 --> 00:52:20,804
Yes.

752
00:52:22,639 --> 00:52:24,933
He came to my school to see me that day.

753
00:52:28,603 --> 00:52:29,980
How did you recognize him?

754
00:52:32,607 --> 00:52:34,484
I just did when I saw him.

755
00:52:37,612 --> 00:52:38,905
Did you talk to him?

756
00:52:39,990 --> 00:52:41,032
No.

757
00:52:42,158 --> 00:52:44,077
I rushed over to you as soon as I saw him.

758
00:52:47,789 --> 00:52:48,707
Why?

759
00:52:50,959 --> 00:52:52,210
I was scared…

760
00:52:56,590 --> 00:52:58,592
that he might go to you.

761
00:53:02,012 --> 00:53:03,638
Or that he might follow me…

762
00:53:08,143 --> 00:53:10,353
and hurt Mom again.

763
00:53:43,929 --> 00:53:47,015
I thought you didn't know
because you were so young.

764
00:53:52,687 --> 00:53:53,563
Right.

765
00:53:55,065 --> 00:53:56,816
I don't know why I remember that.

766
00:54:03,907 --> 00:54:05,575
Why didn't you tell me?

767
00:54:07,160 --> 00:54:08,870
You didn't tell me about it either.

768
00:54:13,083 --> 00:54:14,084
Sorry.

769
00:54:14,668 --> 00:54:17,712
Stop that. Why are you apologizing?

770
00:54:21,508 --> 00:54:23,677
I thought only I remembered it.

771
00:54:30,016 --> 00:54:31,977
Maybe I should have said hello that day.

772
00:54:34,396 --> 00:54:36,439
I shouldn't tell Mom about this. Right?

773
00:54:51,997 --> 00:54:52,956
Mom.

774
00:54:54,916 --> 00:54:57,502
-Did you eat?
-We ate.

775
00:54:57,585 --> 00:54:58,753
What about you?

776
00:54:58,837 --> 00:55:01,047
I said you didn't have to come.
Why are you here?

777
00:55:01,131 --> 00:55:03,008
You don't come when I ask you to.

778
00:55:04,759 --> 00:55:06,344
Go and get changed.

779
00:55:06,928 --> 00:55:10,890
Come on. You were born with good looks.
What's up with the dull outfits?

780
00:55:14,978 --> 00:55:16,730
As for the debt he left behind…

781
00:55:17,647 --> 00:55:19,232
I'll take care of it.

782
00:55:19,733 --> 00:55:21,901
-What do you mean?
-I can pay it off.

783
00:55:21,985 --> 00:55:25,488
Are you crazy?
How do you know this is his only debt?

784
00:55:25,572 --> 00:55:29,492
A lot more creditors might show up
if they hear you're paying it off.

785
00:55:31,411 --> 00:55:34,998
Don't you ever think about it.
Not a penny from you two.

786
00:55:39,210 --> 00:55:41,671
Here's the document.
Stamp it with your seal.

787
00:55:41,755 --> 00:55:43,506
And forget about this.

788
00:55:46,092 --> 00:55:47,218
Do you understand me?

789
00:55:49,012 --> 00:55:49,888
Yes.

790
00:55:52,849 --> 00:55:54,434
What about you?

791
00:55:56,061 --> 00:55:57,103
Yes.

792
00:55:58,730 --> 00:56:01,149
No wonder he showed up in my dreams.

793
00:56:06,029 --> 00:56:07,155
Want some Korean melons?

794
00:56:07,238 --> 00:56:09,074
-I'll go get them.
-Stay here.

795
00:56:14,537 --> 00:56:16,539
At least he kept his promise.

796
00:56:17,540 --> 00:56:20,043
I told him not to find us
until he was dead.

797
00:56:20,752 --> 00:56:21,836
So…

798
00:56:22,921 --> 00:56:25,090
he came back after he died.

799
00:56:31,346 --> 00:56:33,264
That's when I realized.

800
00:56:35,892 --> 00:56:40,647
Mom was scared her whole life
that he might come looking for us.

801
00:56:44,692 --> 00:56:47,362
Mom and my brother…

802
00:56:48,029 --> 00:56:50,073
We all remembered it.

803
00:56:54,202 --> 00:56:57,038
The memories that seemed to be faded away

804
00:56:57,122 --> 00:57:00,667
only seemed so
because I avoided recalling them.

805
00:57:05,088 --> 00:57:06,840
He should have lived a better life.

806
00:57:08,716 --> 00:57:13,221
To live a life without seeing the man
who was once the love of her life,

807
00:57:14,013 --> 00:57:18,101
what did she have to go through?

808
00:57:21,438 --> 00:57:24,023
Tae-jeong, peel them for us.
Be careful with the knife.

809
00:57:28,820 --> 00:57:30,780
Her past love ended up

810
00:57:31,990 --> 00:57:34,659
becoming a knife stuck in our throats.

811
00:57:36,369 --> 00:57:39,372
Was she ever able to cry her heart out?

812
00:57:42,625 --> 00:57:45,670
Did she run the water

813
00:57:46,629 --> 00:57:48,173
even when she was alone?

814
00:58:13,281 --> 00:58:14,282
Mom.

815
00:58:16,201 --> 00:58:17,577
It's okay to cry.

816
00:58:37,805 --> 00:58:41,142
I just got off. I was thinking
about heading over there. Is that okay?

817
00:58:48,233 --> 00:58:50,318
Oh, no. I checked the message too late.

818
00:58:50,944 --> 00:58:54,572
I just had a delicious meal
with my mom. I'm so stuffed.

819
01:00:23,578 --> 01:00:25,121
Can you not come?

820
01:00:25,705 --> 01:00:27,790
I want to spend time with her alone.

821
01:00:28,291 --> 01:00:30,335
Sure. See you tomorrow then.

822
01:00:30,418 --> 01:00:32,587
Let's check out
the beach together next time.

823
01:00:35,006 --> 01:00:37,675
Sure. Let's check out
the beach together next time.

824
01:00:54,651 --> 01:00:55,735
CYCLOSPORINE

825
01:01:40,863 --> 01:01:42,657
What was your temperature this morning?

826
01:01:44,117 --> 01:01:46,160
It was 37.2 degrees Celsius.

827
01:01:47,370 --> 01:01:50,665
Right before I left,
it did go down to 37 degrees.

828
01:01:50,748 --> 01:01:52,333
I think you'll be okay,

829
01:01:52,417 --> 01:01:53,251
JU-WON

830
01:01:53,334 --> 01:01:54,794
but you're on your way, right?

831
01:01:55,795 --> 01:01:58,339
Yes. I'll be there after this signal.

832
01:01:58,423 --> 01:02:00,633
Okay. Let's get you x-rayed
when you get here.

833
01:02:02,093 --> 01:02:03,302
Okay.

834
01:02:03,886 --> 01:02:06,556
Hello? Were you coughing just now?

835
01:02:07,265 --> 01:02:08,766
I thought it was just a fever.

836
01:02:09,475 --> 01:02:10,518
Young-do.

837
01:02:11,185 --> 01:02:13,229
Answer me. Ju Young-do.

838
01:04:23,484 --> 01:04:27,196
Yuddy shows Su Li Zhen

839
01:04:27,280 --> 01:04:29,615
a watch for one minute.

840
01:04:30,449 --> 01:04:33,286
He says that one minute
will be remembered forever.

841
01:04:34,328 --> 01:04:35,997
So this is how I understood it.

842
01:04:36,789 --> 01:04:39,208
"I'll be leaving eventually,

843
01:04:39,917 --> 01:04:42,545
but this one minute is just for you.

844
01:04:43,045 --> 01:04:45,548
No one will take it from you,

845
01:04:45,631 --> 01:04:47,800
and it won't disappear either.

846
01:04:47,884 --> 01:04:51,721
It's a one-minute eternity just for you."

847
